  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "add the minari to the skillet and cook for 2-3 minutes, until tender.",
    "in a small bowl, whisk together the lemon juice and 1 tbsp of olive oil to make the garlic glaze.",
    "add the quinoa to the skillet and stir to combine with the garlic and minari.",
    "season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "top the quinoa mixture with crumbled feta cheese, pitted kalamata olives, and chopped fresh parsley.",
    "drizzle the garlic glaze over the top of the bowl.",
    "serve hot and enjoy!"
